sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/KubeRay
    participant API as K8s API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant MutWebhook as CodeFlare Mutating Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant ValWebhook as CodeFlare Validating Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Controller as CodeFlare Controller
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuthProxy as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Dashboard as Ray Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP (localhost)
    participant RayHead as Ray Head Pod<br/>10001/TCP mTLS
    participant RayWorker as Ray Worker Pod<br/>10001/TCP mTLS

    Note over User,RayWorker: Flow 1: RayCluster Creation with OAuth and mTLS

    User->>API: Create RayCluster CR<br/>Service Account Token
    API->>MutWebhook: Admission Request<br/>K8s API Server mTLS
    MutWebhook-->>API: Inject OAuth proxy + mTLS init containers
    API->>ValWebhook: Validation Request<br/>K8s API Server mTLS
    ValWebhook-->>API: Validate configuration

    Controller->>API: Watch RayCluster events<br/>Service Account Token
    Controller->>API: Create CA Secret<br/>Service Account Token
    Controller->>API: Create OAuth Secret<br/>Service Account Token
    Controller->>API: Create OAuth Service<br/>Service Account Token
    Controller->>API: Create Route/Ingress<br/>Service Account Token
    Controller->>API: Create NetworkPolicies<br/>Service Account Token

    Note over User,RayWorker: Flow 2: User Access to Ray Dashboard via OAuth

    User->>Router: HTTPS Request to Ray Dashboard<br/>443/TCP TLS1.2+
    Router-->>User: Redirect to OpenShift OAuth
    User->>Router: HTTPS Request with OAuth Token<br/>443/TCP TLS1.2+
    Router->>OAuthProxy: Forward Request<br/>8443/TCP TLS1.2+<br/>OAuth Token
    OAuthProxy->>Dashboard: Forward to Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP<br/>Localhost (no auth)
    Dashboard-->>OAuthProxy: Dashboard Response
    OAuthProxy-->>Router: Response
    Router-->>User: Dashboard UI

    Note over User,RayWorker: Flow 3: Ray Worker to Ray Head (mTLS)

    RayWorker->>RayHead: Ray Protocol<br/>10001/TCP<br/>mTLS (Ray cluster CA)
    RayHead-->>RayWorker: Response
    RayWorker->>RayHead: Dashboard metrics<br/>8265/TCP HTTP<br/>Internal cluster
